h3. Problem Definition

When we want to search issues which does not contain some word (e.g. xxx) in a text field (including issues which don't have any value in the field), we're supposed to use the following JQL.

{code}
<FIELD_NAME> !~ "xxx" or <FIELD_NAME> is empty
{code}

However, it is difficult for our customers to know the behavior from [our documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRASOFTWARECLOUD/Advanced+searching+-+operators+reference#Advancedsearching-operatorsreference-DOES_NOT_CONTAINDOESNOTCONTAIN:!~] and some customers assume that the JQL should be without {{is empty}} as follows.

{code}
<FIELD_NAME> !~ "xxx"
{code}

h3. Suggested Solution

The similar thing happens when using {{NOT IN}} operator but a valid example is documented [there|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRASOFTWARECLOUD/Advanced+searching+-+operators+reference#Advancedsearching-operatorsreference-NOT_INNOTIN] as follows.

{code}
FixVersion not in (A, B, C, D) or FixVersion is empty
{code}

It would be better if {{DOES NOT CONTAIN}} operator has such a good example in [the document|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRASOFTWARECLOUD/Advanced+searching+-+operators+reference#Advancedsearching-operatorsreference-DOES_NOT_CONTAINDOESNOTCONTAIN:!~].

h3. Problem Definition
It's currently not possible to specify a project key when using below JQL function:
{code}"Epic Link" in ("Issue Key"){code}
It's only possible to specify an issue key.

h3. Suggested Solution
Add the ability to specify a project key when using the "Epic Link" JQL function.
{code}"Epic Link" in ("Project Key"){code}

Workaround.
Currently the workaround is to specify all the epics of the project when searching.
{code}"Epic Link" in ("ProjectA-EpicA","ProjectA-EpicB","ProjectA-EpicC"){code}

h3. Summary

In some Cloud instances, users are unable to add attachment with the following error:
{noformat}
com.atlassian.jira.issue.attachment.store.media.MediaApiStreamAttachmentStore$FailureMediaApiResponseException: [AttachmentUploadFailure] Could not upload temporary attachment↵Failure: Failure
{cause=java.net.SocketTimeoutException: Read timed out, reason=TRANSPORT_ERROR, message='null', httpStatusCode=null}
{noformat}

h3. Updates

We have identified the root cause and applied the fix. If the problem persist, please contact {{getsupport.atlassian.com}}.

h5.Steps to reproduce
# add a field of type that wouldn't be displayed in a screen to your screen (e.g. Service Desk's _Customer Request Type_, _Custom Google Map Field_);
# open a screen that the field was added, and click *Configure Fields > Where is my field?*;
# look up the field name.

*Expected result:* a message that the field isn't designed to be displayed in screens. 
*Actual result:* a message "The [...] field should be present on the form you are viewing"

